name: SpecimenFromANormallySterileSiteSpecimenTypeSNOMED
title: Specimen from a Normally Sterile Site (Specimen Type)(SNOMED)
purpose: (Clinical Focus: SNOMED code(s) for type of specimen used for laboratory test, such as blood, stool, specimen from a normally sterile site, respiratory specimen.),(Data Element Scope: Specimens for laboratory testing as documented in a clinical record.),(Inclusion Criteria: A normally sterile site is defined as: | blood | bone and bone marrow | cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) | internal body sites | specimen obtained from surgery or aspirate from one of the following: brain, heart, kidney, liver, lymph node, ovary, pancreas, spleen, vascular tissue, vitreous fluid: | joint fluid | includes synovial fluid and needle aspirate or culture of any specific joint: ankle, elbow, hip, knee, wrist | muscle | pericardial fluid | peritoneal fluid | includes abdominal fluid, ascites | pleural fluid | includes chest fluid, thoracentesis fluid),(Exclusion Criteria: None)
